### Fundamental Linear Data Structures
*   Array
*   Dynamic Array (e.g., `std::vector`, `ArrayList`)
*   String
*   Linked List (Singly, Doubly, Circular)
*   Stack
*   Queue
*   Deque (Double-Ended Queue)
*   Hash Table (Hash Map, Dictionary)
*   Hash Set

### Trees
#### Core Tree Structures
*   Binary Tree
*   Binary Search Tree (BST)

#### Self-Balancing Binary Search Trees
*   AVL Tree
*   Red-Black Tree
*   Splay Tree
*   2-3 Tree

#### Specialized Tree-Like Structures
*   Trie (Prefix Tree)
*   Radix Tree (Patricia Tree)
*   B-Tree / B+ Tree
*   Suffix Tree / Suffix Array
*   K-D Tree (K-Dimensional Tree)

### Heaps (Priority Queues)
*   Binary Heap (Min-Heap / Max-Heap)
*   Binomial Heap
*   Fibonacci Heap
*   D-ary Heap

### Graphs
*   Adjacency Matrix
*   Adjacency List
*   Incidence Matrix

### Advanced & Specialized Structures
*   Disjoint Set Union (Union-Find)
*   Segment Tree
*   Fenwick Tree (Binary Indexed Tree)
*   Skip List
*   Bloom Filter
*   Quadtree / Octree
*   Rope

### Composite Structures (Common Interview Patterns)
*   LRU Cache
*   LFU Cache
